com.github.westonpace.jayvee.workflow

Interface Source<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of item to be pulled from the source

    public interface Source<T>
    A source that data can be 'pop'ed from. Sources may block if there is no data yet to be processed.
    See Also:
    Sink, Worker

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T pop()
      Reads the next item from the source.

    • Method Detail

      • pop

        T pop()
        Reads the next item from the source. This may block until an item is available and will throw a BufferEndedException if the source is finished and will never have any more items.
        Returns:
        The next item
        Throws:
        BufferEndedException - This is thrown when there are no more items to be read
